    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Eucalyptus regnans, native to Tasmania and Victoria in Australia. It varies in color from almost white to pale brown, and is used in the manufacture of furniture, joinery, paneling, and flooring.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
